 than the next closest pair.\nWe also show that the Chernoff bound is achieved when at least $r-2$ of the\nstates are pure, improving on a previous result by Nussbaum and Szko{\\l}a.\nFinally, we indicate a number of potential pathways along which a proof (or\ndisproof) may eventually be found that the multi-hypothesis quantum Chernoff\nbound is always achieved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 29 Jan 2014 20:46:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 May 2014 11:09:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 14 Oct 2014 19:32:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-05"}
