s loss in planetesimal collisions is distributed in the bigger\nfragments.\n  Planetesimal fragmentation seems to play an important role in giant planet\nformation. The way in which the mass loss in planetesimal collisions is\ndistributed leads to different results, inhibiting or favoring the formation of\nmassive cores.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Jan 2014 05:00:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-05-21"}
